commentary: Jongwe to Azhar Ali, OUT Nyumbu atones for the dropped catch with a brilliant direct hit! Azhar takes a huge step down the track, and Jongwe shortens his length. He defends, and the ball runs away towards wide second slip. He didn't know where the ball had gone, and starts for a single. I think Shehzad may have said yes, and then no, and by the time Azhar turned back it was too late. Pinpoint throw from Nyumbu to catch him well short.

commentary: Nyumbu to Shoaib Malik, OUT bowled him! Jumped down the track, and slogged in a rather unedifying manner, across the line, his head swivelling all over the place. A touch of Javagal Srinath about that shot. Good ball from Nyumbu too, it went above the batsman's eyeline and dipped below it quickly. Snappy flight, and it turned in sharply from outside off to knock back middle stump

That's just a touch short outside off, and even though it's turning sharply into off stump, Rizwan has time to make room and open his bat face and place that extremely fine, inches to the right of the keeper and find the boundary. commentary: Yasir Shah to Mutumbami, OUT he has four, and he owes it to the catcher! Hafeez has pulled off a stunning one-hander to his right. This was a quicker ball on off stump, Mutumbami plants an open face down on it and it seems like he has eked out an easy single using the pace of the leggie. But Hafeez has stayed low, his reflexes are still sharp and he sticks out the right hand to claim a catch he will remember for a while
